name: Air Fryer Spanish Tortilla
author: Buckwheat Queen
summary: A Spanish tortilla is just as tasty when made in your air fryer. This recipe saves on cleanup and reduces oil from the traditional recipes. Try this nestled in a ciabatta roll with some hot sauce.
ingredients: 1 large potato, peeled and cut into 1-inch cubes
⅛ cup leek, sliced into 1/4-inch pieces
¼ cup grated Pecorino Romano cheese
salt and ground black pepper to taste
⅛ cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley
directions: Rinse potato cubes and put them into a bowl with cold water to soak for about 10 minutes
Preheat an air fryer to 325 degrees F (160 degrees C)
Drain the potatoes and pat dry
Transfer to a bowl and toss with olive oil
Put them into the air fryer basket
Raise the temperature to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C)
Add leek and shake basket again
Cook until leek has softened, about 3 minutes
Meanwhile, whisk eggs, Pecorino Romano cheese, salt, and pepper together in a bowl and pour into a 6-inch, nonstick cake pan
Mix in cooked potatoes and leek
Set cake pan into the air fryer basket
Cook until tortilla has browned on top and the middle no longer jiggles, about 15 minutes
Remove from the air fryer and cool for 5 minutes
Sprinkle with Italian parsley before serving
